{
  "_readme": [
    "Query-content blocklist enforced by QueryBlocklist.kt at four chokepoints:",
    "  1. QueryBankManager.getQueries()   - pre-filter the loaded corpus",
    "  2. MarkovQueryGenerator.generate() - post-generation resample",
    "  3. MarkovQueryGenerator.injectSeedPhrases() - reject user-supplied seeds",
    "  4. SearchPoisonModule.onAction()   - final dispatch gate (skip cycle if matched)",
    "",
    "TWO HARM CLASSES:",
    "  class_a_terms      - illegal / harm-to-others content (bomb recipes, CSAM, etc).",
    "                       Safe to execute-by-humans is NOT a defense; these must never",
    "                       be dispatched under any circumstance.",
    "  self_signal_terms  - benign-to-execute but harmful as synthetic user signal.",
    "                       A 988 query from a real user in crisis is a lifeline; the",
    "                       same query injected as noise creates a false first-person",
    "                       distress flag in broker/government/insurer profiles with",
    "                       real-world downstream consequences (wellness checks, insurance",
    "                       denial, watchlists). ALL entries here must be multi-word",
    "                       phrase anchors to avoid false positives on legitimate",
    "                       research/history/news queries (e.g. 'Cuban Missile Crisis').",
    "",
    "CONTRIBUTOR RULES:",
    "  - No bare single common words (crisis, abuse, kill, bomb, drug).",
    "  - Prefer first-person markers ('my', 'I', 'am I', 'near me') or unambiguous",
    "    specialty terms (988, naloxone, mifepristone).",
    "  - New entries must pass: grep -iF '<entry>' app/src/main/assets/query_banks/*.json",
    "    returning only entries that SHOULD be filtered (run before committing)."
  ],
